{% block content %}

<!-- INTRO SECTION - BEGINS -->
	<section class="col-24">
		<h1>{{ model.title }}</h1>
		<p class="mul-intro-text">Basic Containers are used throughout the site and applications as a starting point for all boxes. Normally they contain base information along with customizeable options. </p>
	</section>
<!-- INTRO SECTION - ENDS -->

<section class="col-24">

	<h3 class="mul-hdr-dbl-rule">
		Example
		<a href="javascript:;" class="mul-icon-size-small mul-icon-mul-arrow-circle-down mul-icon-color-gray-darker mul-icon-position-right mul-float-right related-items-menu"></a>
	</h3>

<!-- BASIC CONTAINER - BEGINS -->
	<div class="col-24 example-min-height">

		<div class="col-6 first">
			<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Basic container</h4>
			{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn" %}
		</div>
		<div class="col-6">
			<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Example with header</h4>
			{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn-header" %}
		</div>
		<div class="col-6">
			<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Example with round corners</h4>
			{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn-header-rounded" %}
		</div>
		<div class="col-6">
			<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Example with drop shadow</h4>
			{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn-header-rounded-shadow" %}
		</div>
	</div>
<!-- BASIC CONTAINER - ENDS -->

<!-- DETAILS SECTION - BEGINS -->
	<div class="col-24">
		<a name="moreDetails"></a>
		<h4 class="mul-hdr-dbl-rule addtional-detail-hdr">Additional Details</h4>
		

		<div class="js-mul-tabs-example mul-tabs">
			{% include "page-tabs" %}
			<div id="tabs-1">
				<p>Containers in general are used to highlight specific areas of content. The Basic Container features 3 components - header, body and footer. These components can be used in any combination - all are not required. Options for this container are rounded corners and drop shadows. A sample of a basic container is the <a href="/objects/inline-search">Inline Search Container</a>.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-2">
				<h5>Components</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>The Basic Container is comprised of the following components:
						<ul>
							<li>Border</li>
							<li>Header (optional)</li>
							<li>Horizontal Line (optional)</li>
							<li>Content</li>
							<li>Background Color</li>
							<li>Rounded Corner (optional)</li>
							<li>Drop Shadow (optional)</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>The border color (#6b90b8) should always be a solid, 1 pixel gray line.</li>
					<li>The headers for Basic Containers can be designated as either h1, h2, or h3. </li>
					<li>The Horizontal Line directly under the Basic Container's header is (#CCCCCC).</li>
					<li>The Background color is #EEEEEE.</li>
				</ul>

				<h5>Sizing and Layout</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>The content margins inside all Mercer Basic Containers will have 15 pixels of padding all around.</li>
					<li>The padding inside a Basic Container from the line under the header to the beginning of the actual content is also 15 pixels.</li>
					<li>Basic Container height and width are variable based on inside content height and width.</li>
				</ul>

				<h5>Grids</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Basic Containers work within the Mercer Evolution Grid System.</li>
					<li>Basic Containers can contain grids inside of them to display and section off data within the container.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-3">
				<p>Technical details go here&hellip;</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-4">
				<ul>
					<li>In the mobile version of this container the width will shrink to span the width of the parent container.</li>
					<li>Font size increases for mobile.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-5">
			<!-- GET CODE - BEGINS -->
				<section class="col-24">

					<h5 class="mul-hdr-rule">HTML</h5>

                    <h5>Basic container</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn" %}</xmp></pre>

                    <h5>Container with header</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn-header" %}</xmp></pre>

                    <h5>Container with rounded corners</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn-header-rounded" %}</xmp></pre>

                    <h5>Container with drop shadow</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/base/boxes/basic-ctn-header-rounded-shadow" %}</xmp></pre>

				</section>
			<!-- GET CODE - ENDS -->
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
<!-- DETAILS SECTION - ENDS -->

</section>
{% endblock %}